            <h2>Learning About Macros</h2>


            <div class="col-container">

                <div class="col">
            <h3>Protein</h3>
            <p>Protein is known as the building blocks of the body. Protein is used to build and
            repair muscle tissue. Protein is used to give your body extra energy when needed.
            </p>
                <h4>Some examples of good protein include</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Seafood</li>
                    <li>Chicken</li>
                    <li>Lean beef</li>
                    <li>Eggs </li>
                </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
            <h3>Fat</h3>
            <p>Fats give you energy as well as helping the body absorb and digest the vitamins that it needs.
                Fatty acids help the body function, but you must make sure that you consume them. <b>BUT,</b> make
                sure to stay away from certain fats that are bad for your health such as <b>Saturated Fats</b>
                and <b>Trans Fats</b>. These fats are in food like pizza, burgers, cookies and other snack food.
            </p>
            <h4>Some examples of good fat include</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Seafood</li>
                <li>Eggs</li>
                <li>Avocaodos</li>
                <li>Almonds </li>
            </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
            <h3>Carbs</h3>
            <p>Most people <i>shiver</i> when they hear the word Carbs. Carbs are the main source of energy that
                the body needs in order to survive. Carbs also supply fiber which can help your body prevent
                stomach problems as well as lower cholesterol and blood sugar. Be careful in which carbs you
                consume though. <b>Simple Carbs</b> often are loaded in sugar and your body doesn't process as well.
                <b>Complex Carbs</b> are healthier for your body and help your burn energy quicker.
            </p>
            <h4>Some examples of good carbs include</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Rice</li>
                <li>Potatoes</li>
                <li>Vegetables</li>
                <li>Fruits </li>
            </ul>
                </div>
