        <h2>Cutting vs. Bulking</h2>
        <div class="col-container">

            <div class="col">
                <h3>Cutting</h3>
                <p>
                    <b>Cutting</b> is the reduction of body fat and you will need to eat less calories
                    in a day than while you are burning while lifting. We call this a <i>caloric deficit.</i>
                    During this time you will need to increase protein to preserve muscle mass. Your workouts can still be
                    heavy, but should also involve some form of cardio as well.
                </p>

            </div>

            <div class="col">
                <h3>Bulking</h3>
                <p>
                    <b>Bulking</b> means to gain weight by increasing muscle mass. You will need
                    to be able to eat more calories a day than you are burning while lifting.
                    We call this a <i>caloric surplus.</i> During this time you will want to eat
                    extra <i>healthy</i> calories, while challenging yourself by lifting heavier.
                </p>

            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <img src="images/BulkCut.jpg" alt="weight" height="300" width="500">
