        <h2>Low Intensity Steady State Cardio vs. High Intensity Interval Cardio</h2>
        <div class="col-container">

            <div class="col">
                <h3>Low Intensity Steady State Cardio</h3>
                <p>
                    <b>LISS</b> involves repetitions of the same movements for long periods of time. This cardio
                form must allow your heart rate to be at a moderate level during the duration of the workout. Some examples
                include walking, jogging, and aerobics.

            </div>

            <div class="col">
                <h3>High Intensity Interval Cardio</h3>
                <p>
                    <b>HIIT</b> involves performing high-intensity activities for a short period of time, followed
                    by periods of low-intensity activities in a cycle. These activities can be completed in just
                    20 minutes! Some of these activities include sprinting, circuit training or Tabata workouts.
                </p>

            </div>
        </div>
